𝐉𝐔𝐒𝐓 𝐈𝐍 | 𝐅𝐄𝐔 𝐈𝐇𝐒𝐍 𝐒𝐭𝐮𝐝𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐂𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐜𝐢𝐥 𝐂𝐚𝐥𝐥𝐬 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐂𝐥𝐚𝐬𝐬 𝐒𝐮𝐬𝐩𝐞𝐧𝐬𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐀𝐜𝐚𝐝𝐞𝐦𝐢𝐜 𝐀𝐝𝐣𝐮𝐬𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬 𝐀𝐦𝐢𝐝𝐬𝐭 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐍𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐰𝐢𝐝𝐞 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐩𝐨𝐫𝐭 𝐒𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐤𝐞

In light of the scheduled nationwide transport strike announced by Piston and Manibela on September 17–19, 2025, the FEU IHSN Student Council has formally submitted a recommendation letter today, September 16, 2025 to the administration requesting the suspension of face-to-face classes and transitioning to online learning. This initiative seeks to prioritize the safety and welfare of students, faculty, and staff who are directly affected by transportation disruptions.

The recommendations highlight the following:

1.Transition of classes to online platforms during the strike
2. Flexible consideration for students with OJT and internships
3. Ensuring accessibility and safety of the IHSN community
4. Alignment with FEU’s institutional values.

The FEU IHSN Student Council stands firm in advocating for the needs of the student body, ensuring inclusivity, safety, and academic continuity amidst external challenges.

Read the full recommendation letter here:
📎 Copy of the [IHSN SC] Transport Strike Petition Letter https://docs.google.com/document/d/1sFXp-seWFO3gStZURsOXS1Rt59tpeAAbPVDxoNq5-EU/edit?usp=drivesdk

Stay tuned for updates, IHSN Tams!

#FEUIHSNSC
#ForgeAhead
#IgnitedAndCentered

In light of the scheduled nationwide transport strike announced by Piston and Manibela on September 17–19, 2025, the FEU IHSN Student Council has formally submitted a recommendation letter today, September 16, 2025 to the administration requesting the suspension of face-to-face classes and transitioning to online learning. This initiative seeks to prioritize the safety and welfare of students, faculty, and staff who are directly affected by transportation disruptions.

The recommendations highlight the following:

1.Transition of classes to online platforms during the strike
2. Flexible consideration for students with OJT and internships
3. Ensuring accessibility and safety of the IHSN community
4. Alignment with FEU’s institutional values.

The FEU IHSN Student Council stands firm in advocating for the needs of the student body, ensuring inclusivity, safety, and academic continuity amidst external challenges.

Read the full recommendation letter here:
📎 Copy of the [IHSN SC] Transport Strike Petition Letter https://docs.google.com/document/d/1sFXp-seWFO3gStZURsOXS1Rt59tpeAAbPVDxoNq5-EU/edit?usp=drivesdk

𝐉𝐔𝐒𝐓 𝐈𝐍 | 𝐅𝐄𝐔 𝐈𝐇𝐒𝐍 𝐒𝐭𝐮𝐝𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐂𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐜𝐢𝐥 𝐂𝐚𝐥𝐥𝐬 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐂𝐥𝐚𝐬𝐬 𝐒𝐮𝐬𝐩𝐞𝐧𝐬𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐀𝐜𝐚𝐝𝐞𝐦𝐢𝐜 𝐀𝐝𝐣𝐮𝐬𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬 𝐀𝐦𝐢𝐝𝐬𝐭 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐍𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐰𝐢𝐝𝐞 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐩𝐨𝐫𝐭 𝐒𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐤𝐞

In light of the scheduled nationwide transport strike announced by Piston and Manibela on September 17–19, 2025, the FEU IHSN Student Council has formally submitted a recommendation letter today, September 16, 2025 to the administration requesting the suspension of face-to-face classes and transitioning to online learning. This initiative seeks to prioritize the safety and welfare of students, faculty, and staff who are directly affected by transportation disruptions.

The recommendations highlight the following:

1.Transition of classes to online platforms during the strike
2. Flexible consideration for students with OJT and internships
3. Ensuring accessibility and safety of the IHSN community
4. Alignment with FEU’s institutional values.

The FEU IHSN Student Council stands firm in advocating for the needs of the student body, ensuring inclusivity, safety, and academic continuity amidst external challenges.

Read the full recommendation letter here:
📎 Copy of the [IHSN SC] Transport Strike Petition Letter https://docs.google.com/document/d/1sFXp-seWFO3gStZURsOXS1Rt59tpeAAbPVDxoNq5-EU/edit?usp=drivesdk

Stay tuned for updates, IHSN Tams!

#FEUIHSNSC
#ForgeAhead
#IgnitedAndCentered

Because when we serve together, we create a future worth traveling for.

𝑻𝒐𝒈𝒆𝒕𝒉𝒆𝒓, 𝒘𝒆 𝒔𝒉𝒂𝒑𝒆 𝒕𝒐𝒎𝒐𝒓𝒓𝒐𝒘’𝒔 𝒕𝒐𝒖𝒓𝒊𝒔𝒎 🌍

On World Tourism Day, PATA Philippines FEU Student Chapter embraces the theme “𝑬𝒎𝒑𝒐𝒘𝒆𝒓𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝑽𝒐𝒍𝒖𝒏𝒕𝒆𝒆𝒓𝒊𝒔𝒎 𝒇𝒐𝒓 𝒂 𝑻𝒓𝒂𝒏𝒔𝒇𝒐𝒓𝒎𝒂𝒕𝒊𝒗𝒆 𝑻𝒐𝒖𝒓𝒊𝒔𝒎 𝑭𝒖𝒕𝒖𝒓𝒆.”

This September, let us celebrate the role of service, unity, and passion in shaping tourism that goes beyond travel—an industry that transforms lives, fosters sustainability, and builds brighter tomorrows.

Because when we serve together, we create a future worth traveling for.
